div.font: In Spring-applications, all requests sent from front-end (such as a login page of organisation overview page) to back-end are received in Spring controllers. The requests and their parameters are then passed to their corresponding Spring services. There are more of those services than just the ones shown on the diagram, such as one for editions and one for projects. This is where all of the processing will be done. Services can call upon JPA-repositories for database transactions, such as for adding, deleting, or otherwise persistent data.
